main event: An object was observed in Wales, Alaska, which was white, irregular in shape, moved erratically at great speed and then disappeared.
interesting points: The object initially appeared like a star before growing larger in size., The movement of the object was erratic and at high speed., Lt. Hanscom from the Dover Radar Lab confirmed there were no radar blips during the time of the sighting., This was classified as an unusual visual observation., The report concludes that there is insufficient information about the sighting.
